olive oil
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 bag thyme
1 clove garlic
1 bag green beans
1 packet black garlic
1 packet mayonnaise
½ packet panko breadcrumbs
20 g butter
1 tbs plain flour
¾ cup milk
¼ tsp salt
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet Premium Fillet Steak
3 pear
1 packet pecans
1 bag Classic Oat Mix
1 packet Dark Chocolate Chips
½ packet cream

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Place peeled pumpkin pieces on a lined oven
tray, drizzle with olive oil and season with salt
and pepper. Toss to coat, then spread out evenly
and roast until just tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, pick and thinly slice thyme leaves.
Finely chop garlic. Trim green beans. Peel
black garlic.
• In a small bowl, mash black garlic with a fork
until smooth, then add mayonnaise. Stir to
combine and set aside.
• In a medium bowl, combine panko
breadcrumbs (see ingredients) with a drizzle of
olive oil, then season.

• When the pumpkin has 5 minutes remaining,
heat a large frying pan over medium heat.
Cook the butter, thyme and garlic until
fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add the plain flour and cook, stirring, until a
thick paste forms, 2 minutes.
• Remove the pan from heat, then slowly whisk
in the milk until smooth. Stir through the salt
and grated Parmesan cheese, then season with
pepper.
• Add the roasted pumpkin and gently stir to
coat. Transfer mixture to a baking dish.
• Evenly top with the panko crumb, then bake
until golden and bubbling, 10-15 minutes.

• Meanwhile, wash and dry the frying pan, then
return to high heat. Season premium fillet
steak, then add to the hot pan. Sear steak until
browned, 1 minute on all sides.
• Transfer to the lined oven tray and roast for
8-10 minutes for medium or until cooked to
your liking.
• Remove the steak from the oven and set aside
to rest.

TIP: The meat will keep cooking while it rests!

• While the steak is roasting, return the frying pan
to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
Cook green beans, tossing, until just tender,
5-6 minutes. Season to taste.

TIP: Add a dash of water to help speed up the
cooking process.

• Slice premium fillet steak.
• Divide pumpkin-thyme gratin, steak and greens
between plates.
• Pour any resting juices over steak and serve with
black garlic mayo. Enjoy!